Resume Quality Review and Polish Pass
Timestamp: 2026-06-10T174300Z
Repository: szmyty/resume
Scope: resume.pdf, resume.tex, resume.sty, sections/*.tex, profiles/*.yaml, scripts/*.py, specs/*.md

Overall Assessment
- The resume has strong technical credibility, clear mission-impact projects, and distinctive research signal.
- The primary gaps were scanability, ATS heading consistency, and a CI-risk fallback YAML parser path.

Strengths
- High-impact, real-world engineering outcomes (USAID/NATO/law-enforcement contexts).
- Clear systems/platform architecture signal.
- Verifiable research publication with DOI and ORCID.
- Maintainable modular publication repository structure.

Findings
[HIGH] Missing "Experience" section heading in rendered resume content reduced ATS heading consistency and quick-scan readability.
[HIGH] Experience bullets were verbose and buried top impact signal.
[HIGH] Fallback YAML parser did not support folded block scalars (e.g., description: >), creating CI fragility when PyYAML is unavailable.
[MEDIUM] Publication entry used line-break formatting that can reduce extraction consistency.
[MEDIUM] Section separators and heading whitespace required tightening for denser scan flow and improved page utilization.
[MEDIUM] Summary was broader than necessary and could be more concise/high-signal.
[LOW] Skills ATS alignment could be incrementally improved with role-aligned terminology already supported by experience content.

Implemented Recommendations
[HIGH] Added explicit Experience heading in sections/experience.tex.
[HIGH] Reordered/tightened experience bullets to front-load strongest outcomes while preserving factual accuracy.
[HIGH] Updated scripts/build.py simple YAML fallback parser to support folded/literal block scalars.
[MEDIUM] Refined publications wording/formatting for cleaner extraction and readability.
[MEDIUM] Removed page numbering footer in resume.sty per review feedback.
[MEDIUM] Tightened section separator styling and section spacing in resume.sty to improve whitespace utilization.
[MEDIUM] Reordered MIT experience bullets to place USAID impact before humanitarian deconfliction.
[MEDIUM] Moved Publication and ORCID links onto dedicated lines in the Publications section for cleaner extraction.
[MEDIUM] Tightened summary wording for faster recruiter scan.
[LOW] Added "Distributed Systems" to skills backend/data group for ATS keyword coverage.

Remaining Opportunities
- Optional future enhancement: implement profile-level summary overrides in build rendering for tighter variant targeting.
- Optional future enhancement: further trim education bullets if one-page prioritization is desired.

Priority Order
1) Preserve impact-first bullet ordering and concise wording.
2) Keep ATS-readable heading structure and publication formatting stable.
3) Maintain resilient YAML parsing behavior in environments without PyYAML.
